Local Ubuntu Server-la Terraform & Ansible Setup
Step by step, entha folder-la என்ன பண்றோம் nu clear-a solren! 🙏
🖥️ PHASE 1 — Ubuntu Server Ready Pannu
Step 1 — System Update
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
🔧 PHASE 2 — Tools Install Pannu
Step 2 — Terraform Install
# Hashicorp key add pannu
wget -O- https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com/gpg | \
  sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg

# Repository add pannu
echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg] \
  https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com $(lsb_release -cs) main" | \
  sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/hashicorp.list

# Install pannu
sudo apt update && sudo apt install terraform -y

# Version check
terraform --version
Step 3 — AWS CLI Install
# Download
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"

# Unzip
sudo apt install unzip -y
unzip awscliv2.zip

# Install
sudo ./aws/install

# Version check
aws --version
Step 4 — Ansible Install
sudo apt install ansible -y

# Version check
ansible --version
Step 5 — kubectl Install (EKS-ku)
# Download
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"

# Install
sudo install -o root -g root -m 0755 kubectl /usr/local/bin/kubectl

# Version check
kubectl version --client
🔑 PHASE 3 — AWS Credentials Setup
Step 6 — AWS Console-la Key Create Pannu
1. AWS Console → IAM → Users → உன்னோட User select pannu
2. Security Credentials tab → Click pannu
3. Access Keys → Create Access Key → CLI select pannu
4. Access Key ID & Secret Access Key — COPY PANNIKO!
Step 7 — Ubuntu-la AWS Configure Pannu
aws configure
AWS Access Key ID:     AKIA************  ← உன்னோட key paste pannu
AWS Secret Access Key: ******************  ← secret paste pannu
Default region name:   ap-south-1          ← Mumbai (or உன் region)
Default output format: json
✅ Verify pannu:
