📋 PHASE 7 — Ansible Setup
Step 22 — Ansible Folder-ku Po
cd ~/my-infra/ansible
Step 23 — Inventory File Create Pannu
EC2 IP addresses — terraform output-la vandhadha use pannu!
nano inventory.ini
[webservers]
server1 ansible_host=13.235.x.x ansible_user=ec2-user ansible_ssh_private_key_file=~/.ssh/my-key-pair.pem
server2 ansible_host=65.0.x.x ansible_user=ec2-user ansible_ssh_private_key_file=~/.ssh/my-key-pair.pem
⚠️ 13.235.x.x and 65.0.x.x — idha உன்னோட actual EC2 IP-la replace pannu!
Step 24 — Playbook Create Pannu
nano playbook.yml
---
- name: Web Server Setup
  hosts: webservers
  become: yes

  tasks:
    - name: System update
      yum:
        name: "*"
        state: latest

    - name: Nginx install
      yum:
        name: nginx
        state: present

    - name: Nginx start
      service:
        name: nginx
        state: started
        enabled: yes

    - name: Docker install
      yum:
        name: docker
        state: present

    - name: Docker start
      service:
        name: docker
        state: started
        enabled: yes

    - name: Sample page create
      copy:
        content: "<h1>Server {{ inventory_hostname }} is Running!</h1>"
        dest: /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
